📋 Copy and Paste this Prompt into your AI Coder:

Role & Context: Act as an Expert C# WPF desktop developer. I am building a Pawn
Broker ERP targeting .NET 8.0. The app will run entirely from a USB Thumbdrive
(offline-first, portable, single-file publish). I need you to generate the
foundational skeleton and boilerplate code using the MVVM pattern (via
CommunityToolkit.Mvvm).

Database Requirements:

1.  Use Entity Framework Core with SQLite.
2.  Implement SQLCipher for database encryption to protect the local .db file in
    case the thumb drive is lost.
3.  Enforce WAL Mode (Write-Ahead Logging) via EF Core configuration (PRAGMA
    journal_mode=WAL;). This is critical to prevent database corruption if the
    user suddenly yanks the thumbdrive out during an operation.

UI & Navigation Requirements:

1.  Login Flow: The app must start with LoginWindow.xaml. Upon successful
    authentication, it should close the Login Window and open MainWindow.xaml.
2.  Main Navigation: MainWindow.xaml must have a modern Side Navigation Menu on
    the left, and a Frame on the right to load Pages.
3.  The Side Navigation must include exactly these buttons/menu items:
      - Dashboard
      - New Pledge
      - Redeem Pledge
      - Manage Pledges
      - Part Payment
      - Customers
      - Settings

Tasks for you:

1.  Give me the .csproj file with the necessary NuGet packages for EF Core
    SQLite, SQLCipher, and the MVVM Community Toolkit.
2.  Write the AppDbContext.cs showing exactly how to apply the SQLCipher
    password and the WAL PRAGMA on initialization.
3.  Write App.xaml.cs to show how to wire up the DB creation and launch the
    LoginWindow.
4.  Write the XAML and ViewModels for the LoginWindow (with a fake login command
    that opens MainWindow) and the MainWindow (with the Side Nav and frame
    routing).

🛠️ Key NuGet Packages You Will Need

When you start building this, these are the exact packages the AI should include
in your project to make SQLCipher and WAL work:

  - CommunityToolkit.Mvvm (For clean, boilerplate-free UI logic)
  - Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite (The base SQLite provider)
  - SQLitePCLRaw.bundle_e_sqlcipher (This is the specific package that replaces
    standard SQLite with the encrypted SQLCipher engine)

💡 Pro-Tip for the WAL Mode on a Thumbdrive:

When the AI generates the AppDbContext, make sure the OnConfiguring method looks
something like this to ensure WAL mode and encryption are active:

protected override void OnConfiguring(DbContextOptionsBuilder optionsBuilder)
{
    // The password encrypts the database file
    var connectionString = "Data Source=PawnERP.db;Password=YourSecurePassword123;";
    
    optionsBuilder.UseSqlite(connectionString);
}

// To enable WAL, you run this when the database is created/initialized
public void InitializeDatabase()
{
    this.Database.Migrate(); // Or EnsureCreated()
    
    // This protects against sudden USB removal corruption
    this.Database.ExecuteSqlRaw("PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL;");
    
    // Highly recommended for USB drives to reduce write frequency
    this.Database.ExecuteSqlRaw("PRAGMA synchronous=NORMAL;"); 
}
